The majority of the Supervisory Board members had concluded that the message sent was that suicide should not be seen as a solution to life crises.
"The majority of the Supervisory Board takes into account the fact that the consequences of the programme "Dupont le midi" would have addressed a sensitive issue in a family-friendly and appropriate way."
Therefore, he was seized with no blame on his person.
The final issue was the statements related to the earthquake in Haiti.
In this regard, Stéphane Dupont and Jean-René Dufort had delivered a media debate that has caused a lot of reactions.
The CHOI moderator had declared not to have donated in favour of Haiti's assistance, since it was not certain that the needy would actually receive the money.
