In Copenhagen last year, large emitters such as the United States, China, Europe and others, including Canada, had committed themselves to voluntary reduction plans that would cut global FCKW emissions from 53 Gt to 49 Gt.
However, from this balance sheet, 5 Gt would still have to be subtracted in order to stabilise the climate increase by 2 degrees Celsius from today until 2020, in order to prevent it from being out of control.
In the white light bulbs 95% of the energy emanates in the form of heat, and the remaining 5% produce the light.
With compact light bulbs, energy consumption is reduced by 75%, with the new LED light bulbs, this energy requirement is reduced by twice again.
